LT-GEE Guide Welcome Documentation by Justin Braaten of Oregon State University’s eMapR Lab 2018/06/11 This site is a guide to the Google Earth Engine implementation of the LandTrendr spectral-temporal segmentation algorithm. Jump right in - plot a segmented time series or map disturbance with a GUI! A huge thanks goes out to the engineers working on Google Earth Engine. This wouldn’t have been possible without your help! Some sections are still under construction (6/11/18) - check back frequenty in the coming month for additional UI applications and shortcut functions. You might try doing a hard refresh on the site to make sure you see recent changes (what you’re looking at might be a previously cached version of the site)
